        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–945</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                            State</gloss> to the Director of the Office of Far Eastern Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vincent</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-10">December 10,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Vincent</hi>: The President has approved the statements
                    given to me.<note n="32" xml:id="d551fn32">See memorandum of December 10, <ref target="#pg_763">p. 763</ref>.</note> I have told him to hold them and
                    unless he hears from me to the contrary to use them. If Marshall makes any
                    suggested changes such changes must be communicated to the President.</p>
                <p>The President also approved our memorandum to the War Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J[<hi rend="smallcaps">ames</hi>] F. B[<hi rend="smallcaps">yrnes</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
